data.title: Reverberations Session 4
data.description:
Archived on 2025-10-19, this archive contains 1143 messages between 10:01:14 PM to 3:15:32 AM.
					It has 65 dice rolls.

messages.content: Reverberations - Session 4
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Somewhere in New Mexico, 2006.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hmmppphhhh!!!! Hnnnnnnnmphh!!!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The thin, bald man is duct-taped very tight to a wooden chair.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sweat is flooding down from his forehead. The rancid, burning New Mexican heat is sizzling through the gaps on the roof.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A man enters from an adjacent room.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Followed by another.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He is holding a rusty, crude machete. He seems nervous, hesitating to take a step forward.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Cmon bro."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You gotta do this."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"HNGHNGH!!!!"

The man, seemingly not understanding Spanish, is trying his hardest to break free.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The sight of a rusty machete in the wrong hands needs no elaboration.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "This is messed up, broâ€¦"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The older brother grabs him by the shoulder for a few words of encouragement.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "No one fucks with us."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Come on."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Here, this will take the edge off."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He produces a keybump of white powder on a stilletto, holding it close to the mans nose.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It hits like a truck in an instant, he heaves once and looks for somewhere to hold onto to regain his bearings.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The innocent gleam in his eye vanishes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "YOU MOTHERFUCKER!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "FUCK YOU!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "HIIIIIIIIEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE!!!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Far-off traffic backdrops the savage sounds of flesh being cleaved into pieces.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Multistory parking garage, Albuquerque NM. May 07 2008.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right back where we were. In the middle of a huge mess.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The coroner is unfolding a stretcher for Damien.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Schrader is giggling at the photos of the boys dead body. Looks like the hamhandedness of DEA agents was not just a rumor.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You may act.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Has the vehicle been searched yet?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Wouldn't hurt to ask.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Anyone check that thing?" Finnegan points at the car, asking nobody in particular.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "It's a pimpmobile. Was idling when we got here."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You may move around.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon produces a pair of nitrile gloves and puts them on.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "No shit." Gloves on. If it's idling, we have the keys, and Finnegan'll check the trunk, glove box, floor mats. 5 minutes or less.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Before we do that, something to get out of the way.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle heard a commotion between the gatekeeper and the cops, looks like something was up with the camera system. He is working on it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug is trying to talk to the gatekeeper.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right. Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll Search, Public.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: The cop, with a laminate, is trying to take pictures of the body.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Without realizing, you step on a thin puddle of blood.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "HEY!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ah, shit."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He looks deathly annoyed with you, but you're in a three-piece suit and he is not.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He grumbles and goes back to work.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan. The car is indeed a pimpmobile, but quite the tasteful one. The upholstery looks genuinely nice. Unbecoming of a run of the mill criminal.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cashmere and velvet seats. Matte cream dash. It's fucking nice, in short.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Not much to look at in the alcoves of the cabin but you realize you could pull prints off of the steering wheel.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If it's nice, that makes me think it's either reported stolen or registered to the actual owner. But we'll take prints from the wheel and the passenger interior handle - great place for a thumbprint.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: It's pretty clean on the inside too, save for the traces of frequent smoking on the roof.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You haven't pulled a print since Quantico. You don't have a forensics kit.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Do we have one in the car?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You're surrounded with cops.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sure, someone here definitely does. Any luck in the obvious spots? Looking for blood or debris, what seat Lucas was transported in.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: No need to roll Search for a second time. If there is a clue, you really can't see it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A second opinion may be a good idea.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You got anything man?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Let me get a second set of eyes on this."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon goes around, having seen the blood mishap.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "â€¦And they either left on foot or in a second vehicle, if that wasn't obvious."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon, Forensics Public with +20%.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "No shit."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8
leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: The complete lack of clues in and around this vehicle may be another tell to a man of your experience.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What's going on here?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A crime scene is usually a story. What you're looking at is disjointed pieces with no connecting lines in between.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Something to think about.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It looks like the body was dumped here, right? As opposed to the injuries happening on-scene.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Have I had a chance to look at the body yet?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: It doesn't take a genius to assess the traumatic extent of the injuries. Damien is in fact "fucked up" but there is way too little blood around to indicate it's been done here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No Cliff.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You've been staring at it from a distance.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If there isn't anything significant to be gathered from looking at the injuries I'll look in the car from the drivers side.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: As you figure out your action, I should address David's little trot around the entire parking lot. David, retroactively roll Search Public.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

6'5. Skinny. Blonde, blue eyes. Disproportionate long arms. Wide face and clavicles.

was investigating federal criminal audit

money laundering. lots of incoming subscriptions, library unexpected, unjustified for the area.

turns out its actually large library book club

tracked missing person, the book club president

investigated their domicile

found entire place ransacked and a book with most pages ripped out

found some pages that go against what he had learned during his cherished study of history

case ends inconclusive

started researching it in free time

DG's Carnivore-fork protocol detected his questions, silent alert is raised

he is contacted, debriefed thoroughly

several points he raises are analyzed and cross-referenced as useful deductions

investigation think-tank permits transfer of federal asset to DG

instruction and briefing commences, works on minor cases

messages.content: Looks just like the usual business day around here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You get a few stares as you walk, but it's nothing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No need for another search or forensics roll, for your expertise in anatomy you immediately recognize that both the drivers and the shotgun seats are adjusted for people a foot or more shorter than Damien.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Hell, you fit in just fine.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Anything in the trunk? He was either there or in the back.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Just a lug wrench and jumper cable. We already took it into evidence."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The extra wheel compartment is pried open, nothing interesting down there either.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'm sure they'll provide a fascinating story."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Feel free to pitch in any time."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He scoffs and goes back to his notes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The coroner lifts Damien onto the stretcher and begans walking him towards the ambulance outside with the paramedics.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A cop follows them.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Seems like the shotgun and driver seats are adjusted for Damien's height. Car's clean so it's unlikely it was used to dump the body."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Figure they picked him up here, then dropped the dead body at the same place?"
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: The guy with the laminate walks past Schrader and out of the crime scene.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Any return on the plates?" Finnegan asks the detective.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Not yet, probably not until lunch break. Same with the prints."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There's a chalk outline where Damien used to be.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan will go call into ABQ dispatch to run the plates and the VIN to make sure they match and see who this is registered to. It's getting towed either way, but maybe someone familiar will pop up.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "They left the car idling either because they had to get out of dodge and forgot to pull out the keys - unlikely OR they wanted the cadaver to be found - likely."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
You can hear the news anchor speak as Damien's stretcher is exiting the scene.

"â€¦KOA-TV has arrived on the scene as soon as possible to capture this young men who has allegedly been the victim of a gang related murderâ€¦"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Vultures arrived, looks alike. Well, I don't think we're going to get anything here that we won't get from the coroner or forensics."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Earle got that CCTV footage yet?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
Earle brushes past you before going out the parking lot for a proper morning coffee.

"It's all fucked, retard IT guy updated the system but didn't realize it messed up the camera software. It didn't record and most likely hasn't been recording for months."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Fucking hell."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "What the fuck, man." McCannon just raises his hands behind his head.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: What the fuck indeed, considering this is New Mexiraq.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "How do they know the cameras were down?"
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Jesus Christ." Finnegan massages his forehead.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Well, there must've been a live feed it's just none of it got backed up in any way."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Was there security? Did they see anything?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
Doug comes back from the questioning.

"Guy says he hasn't seen or heard nothing, no gunshots, no screams. He's crying his guts out, saying he's innocent, mame wey."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "They're taking him in for a statement but I don't think they'll keep him in overnight."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah, yeah, they love that no sabo bullshit."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Lowest common denominator security stuff. I'd be surprised if he saw anything other than the inside of his eyelids."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Everyone but David, Roll Luck. Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a â€œ

catastrophic hemorrhage.â€ Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBIâ€™

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what sheâ€™d seen on her husbandâ€™

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldnâ€™t. They had already erased her husbandâ€™s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didnâ€™t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husbandâ€™s death wasnâ€™t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: McCannon and Finnegan are still turning the inside out of the vehicle. Doug is checking in with his notes, perched over them.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha, smile for TV.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: TV?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: The cameraman.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He's pointing it at you now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha is caught unaware as the cameraman films her, and she turns and gives a faint smile as she notices.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: The cameraman turns back to the anchor without incident.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right, everyone else, it looks like it's time for a word with Schrader and then to blast off.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Unless you have a better idea.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He's talking to his top guy while shooting occasional stares at you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I got nothing. Can Cliff make sure this autopsy gets done tonight-tonight?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: That guy smells like brewer's yeast for some reason. McCannon doesn't really have much to exchange aside from pleasantries right now.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He's obviously expecting a word from you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Go on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well, guy who disappears off the face of the earth in club owned by the most obviously cartel affiliated Mexican turns up here next to an idling blingwagon."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "If this isn't a message I don't know what is."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Hehe, I'm guessing an arrest is soon."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's all splayed out there, but looks like your trafficking thing might be falling apart."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Who trafficks a dead body?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. HUMINT, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: He is fucking with you. Looking for an opening in your narrative, obviously Mexicans killing people when they can't pay to get from point A to point B is routine.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Coyotes, that's who."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Especially when you can't pay."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Doing a white kid in is quite the move, though."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "That's true, but I think whoever you'll arrest will just be some fall-guy low rank cholo, otherwise they wouldn't be this fuckin' sloppy."

messages.content: "There's some dumb fuckers out there, but this dumb?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "It isn't sloppy, it's a statement. You fuck around, something bad happens, and the leftovers are public." He points over his shoulder at the news camera. "The message is sent."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "My point exactly."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
"Probably. Hey, it looks like time for the third coffee of the day."

He nudges Gomez with his elbow.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Don't shit yourselves off those espressos."

messages.content: "Yeah I don't know what the fuck they say," McCannon mutters to himself.

messages.content: Without a doubt, that explanation came off extremely awkward but enough to put a stop to the conversation.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A task force after low-level cholosâ€¦ who knows how that would look on paper.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's 10:30 AM. You're free to act.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan spends the drive out talking about Tcho-Tchos. Better than sitting in silence and brooding over the mystery of Damien Lucas' reappearance.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Drive out where and with who?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David listens to the Tcho-Tcho talk, curious about their history.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: The radio sounds more interesting than that to you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
Well, let's see who's going where.
1. Is Cliff going to the expedited autopsy?
2. Did Earle successfully rat that computer in the club? I remember it being mentioned, don't remember the outcome.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Paramore. Cool, not taytay this time.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cliff.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your action?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The body is being brought to ABQPD Morgue.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: khoka is afk
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: I can do the autopsy, but is it really necessary for me to be doing it?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: YOU have the M.D. at the end of your name.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It probably isn't going to get done in a timeframe that's productive or helpful to us if you don't go. Who knows what their schedule and backlog looks like.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Yeah, if me going to it makes things go faster, I'll do it.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: So I'll do the autopsy.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: khoka is back
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Cliff. The autopsy will take until afternoon to be complete.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The thing about Earle, can you elaborate on that?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I can go back in the log but I remember it being mentioned that he might've been able to set the club owner's computer (the one with the security program and personal email) to keylog or build a record we could collect later.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Low importance if no.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: I know what you're talking about. Earle pulled some personal files off that computer, but did not install a backdoor or keylogger or anything like that. The files are of no consequence to your investigation.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right on.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Right. Where are you driving actually.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You and David.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yes.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Didn't Finnegan want to spin the block on Tcho Tchos?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He's ranting about a Chinese ethnic group you've never heard of before as you trudge through the morning traffic.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: But I really need to know where you are HEADED!
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan explains, in brief, that he thinks our two "ethnicity unknown" Oriental gentlemen of interest in the case are Tcho-Tchos. There aren't too many in the US, and he and David scoped out a business owned by some in the chi-town.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: So you're driving to Chinatown?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We made contact with a juvenile, female. Store is closed for a few days. Do you think it's worth another rollby?" McCannon's call.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Am I in the car with them right now?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Yes, you three are riding.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "What does your gut tell you?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "It tells me that the odds of an extreme minority group living in New fucking Mexico without ties to, coincidentally, organized crime by the same group, are astronomically low."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Slim to none to fucking none."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Then it's time for Big Trouble in Little China."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You've made several trips around the International District in the SUV.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You went past the store twice. It's still closed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's pretty much the same as you left it yesterday. Mostly a trail mix of Asian ethnic groups in a few square acres of land.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I don't think we're going to see any traffic unless it's the female or another relative. The way I see it, if we can get them to open the door, wellâ€¦ It's dirty, and we'll have to figure out PC if anyone asks." He nervously taps on the armrest.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Crime out in the open here is uncommon. You'd have to go to a Negro neighbourhood for that. But for NM, you know what the difference is. Nonetheless everything is discreet as this is a high drug trafficking region and criminals are usually smarter than, say, a bag of rocks.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: So far a peaceful day in Chinatown. Lunch hour is approaching and there are 2-3 good noodle joints nearby, according to Google.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We smelled weed. Chinese medicinal weed."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "That's our PC."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You're not going to sniff out weed in a Chinese neighbourhood unless you're a substance sniffing K9. Even then it's quite hard. Exhaust fumes and ginseng aroma invade your nostrils.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Luckily the wet market isn't that big.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yeah, no shit we're not going to smell weed. It's called lying.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: If there's a lawsuit on the tail end, we won't be there to sit in the courtroom. Finnegan is suggesting we get them to open the door and force entry.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David nods to the mentioned plan.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: If you went to the right neighbourhood you'd know immediately that weed is being cultivated in residential zones around. Anyhow.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan. It's highly unlikely you'll get anything useful from a bedridden old man who knows basic English if you decide to drag him out of his bed to search his store with no warrant. Even worse if you decide to physically break in, at daytime nonetheless.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There has got to be other angles of approach to this, other leads to chase.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan is stuck down a rabbit hole of a novel narcotic being imported or synthesized by foreign nationals. Anyone else got any bright ideas?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll INT.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: Mole mentioned that Pastor is ex-military. No way to pull that one off without leaving a paper trail.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The setback here is that you don't know how to get to that information in New Mexico without the help of federal information networks. In this case, the DEA's.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Would mothafuckin' Earle know?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You have not told Earle about it, but he is willing to share his log-in to get the deed done.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You don't really need his help for this one besides that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A phone call would be enough when time comes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yeah, sure.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: My guess for the Tcho Tcho situation is that if there's one there's more.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Luck, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If we drive around slowly enough or park up and take a brisk walk around the area we should be able to find more Tcho Tcho signs.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: Finnegan figures it's probably one of one.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: As you browse your BlackBerry over lunch, you glance that Cho tsu-tsao, spokesperson for Tcho Tcho Community, will be on Oprah Winfrey Show tonight.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What are the odds?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Disturbing.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David. Ideas?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David says, "These people can't be alone here. Old man and his daughter, and one of them sick. Surely there must be some sort of young nephew around, and he will be sure to visit."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: David, "We could wait and look, but it might be a waste of time."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Let's just ask around at the businesses across the street. It's that simple. Is the place rarely patronized? Visitors after hours?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: If it was on paper the first ones to visit them would be ICE, you gather. You're in illegal immigrant heaven, a few levels behind Miami.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right. We're going to do the culminative chinatown search in one go.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon, you have the lead. Blind search with +20%
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: No wards like Finnegan has seen on the doorsill, but you do catch sight of a couple of really odd and disturbing gang graffiti.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Check this out," McCannon points to the graffiti.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's like a Japanese oni mask face, distorted to have a slightly rounder face and an infinitely more malicious stare.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Indescribable characters are adjacent to it. They are not Chinese and can not be crossreferenced to Finnegan's book.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Looks like you're getting closer.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David takes a closer look, trying to recognize any sort of resemblance to anything he has previously seen.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Figure this is our Tong's backyard?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Maybe. Can you translate that shit?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He can't, even if he did his best. It must be some initiate kind of thing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He shakes his head grimly and offers that it might be analogous to an English second language learner trying to decipher deep gangland cursive grafitti script.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Apt. Moving the time ahead a bit, you ask about the tea shop.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Every response you get is in English. The worker class here is mostly second and third generation immigrant.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's a dinghy but frequented place by the community.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No one remarks it as "shady" or "gangster". Maybe it's because their silence is bought way before you came here?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can't say like this.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The sun passes overhead and prepares its course downward.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Realistically, they just don't want us busting up their after-hours mahjong game.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Or grandpa's game, in any case.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: The time is 15:00.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon gets a call. You don't immediately recognize it, but you realize it's actually the lab tech calling you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You have the sinking feeling that you didn't left a great impression on Bakersfield.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Anyhow, the plates have a match.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Fuck Bakersfield, fat fucker.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Ever heard that you should never chalk up to malice what can be explained by incompetence?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Every single fucking cop in this city reminds me of that."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "The heat's melting their brains, doesn't help that half of them are bald."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "This city sucks. It's like Arizona, but worse."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I should let you know before I forget the details, both the plates and the prints match to one Domingo Molina, 28 ans. Sentenced to 6 years for aggravated assault in 2003, got out in 2 due to overcrowding. This world sucks. There's already an APB out on him, and considering how ASAC might be onto something, this could not hurt being done black bag style.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle pulled his residential, it's right in the middle of the hood, La Mesa. You reckon the cops won't go in there for a myriad of reasons, mostly due to disinterest.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They don't have the information K-cell has. For them it's just a criminal investigation concerning an ex-addict now. Which means next to fuckall.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Think on that. Now, we take a deeper look into what they did to the boy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cliff. You borrow a labcoat and enter the morgue. The coroner has nothing of note to say other than a preliminary examination, listing severed tendons and whatnot.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'll look at the most obvious wounds first.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: The most obvious ones don't need a roll and you've already been given that in handout form.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The limbs are carefully severed at tendon joints and there seem to be four neat little holes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They are not chopped apart, deep cuts.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Has the cause of death been determined yet?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Officially, gunshot to heart.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: All four are pass-through and one goes right past the tricuspid valve.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Are there any notable cuts that could be considered torture? Not aimed at killing him?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Other than the limbs.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Roll Forensics. Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Whether or not a wound was inflicted with intent to torture and not to kill is quite an easy tell. There are no more cuts across his body than what is listedâ€¦ exceptâ€¦
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There is a chain-shaped rash on the back of his neck, like something was yanked out.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's partial, caused a very minor laceration but that's it. Doesn't seem cause for suffocation.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The most obvious answer is hair, no?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: What?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Would hair being yanked out cause a rash like that?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: No, it's very obviously chain-shaped.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Not vaguely.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Aah, like that.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Literally.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: I see.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You should get to the meat and potatoes of it instead of dallying around. Your tools are ready on a counter nearby.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Then I'll start by making an incision on the chest.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: We'll check the heart out.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You make the usual Y-incision. Everything comes out in neat parts. The holes on his chest look gnarly.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I run my perfectly qualified brain to determine if he really did die from the gunshot to the heart.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You'll have to dig in deeper. Surgery, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Should be easy.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Your examination reveals extensive blood loss and oxygen deprivation. Without a doubt this man died from his heart getting poked through.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You also notice thatâ€¦
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The wound tunnels.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They curve about a degree down from the front out the back.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Can a bullet do them with internal ricochet or something?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Or is itâ€¦ unnatural.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: This is not ricochet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Whatever poked through him was a curved object.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: But wasn't the entry wound a bullet hole?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: That's what the coroners report says.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The body wasn't cut open until you got here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What'd I see before cutting him open?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You saw the same thing as everyone else!
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Now that he's open in front of you you have more answers.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is there an exit wound on the back?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Or is it curved and stops internally.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Yes, all four of them exit out the back, that's how you can tell there was a deflection.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: As you move closer to the body, you notice the cleanness of the cuts on his limbs and tendons.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They seem to be made with a very, very sharp surface.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can't think of any scalpels that can just dig in that deep without harming the surrounding tissue in some way.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A large and crazy sharp knife could have achieved this.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Are the wounds on the arms reminiscent of damage with a curved blade?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Not enough tells to reach that conclusion.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The wound is tooâ€¦ insubstantial to leave a mark that says "yeah, that's the product of a curved object" unlike the passthroughs in his chest cavity.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Those ones have their own tale.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: As you mull over it, you go back to his file and check it again.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: His tox screen is attached. Positive for caffeine, nicotine, escitalopram and MDMA.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doesn't seem relevant to the wounds.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Not immediately. Then you remember about the two ounce bags of (partially) MDMA pills in this mans posession and his possible gang connections.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You cut, chop and slash your way through the guy. It's nothing new to you. Now is the time for the brain.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: How do you approach it?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Are there any wounds on the head, other than the chain rash around the neck?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: None, save for some years-old scars.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Should be normal. I cut it open to see if it's as  I expect.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Maybe some brute damageâ€¦
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: BZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZ
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The skull flips open from the top like a jar. You take his brain out to examine it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha. Roll Medicine, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI
messages.content:
Success

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a â€œ

catastrophic hemorrhage.â€ Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBIâ€™

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what sheâ€™d seen on her husbandâ€™

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldnâ€™t. They had already erased her husbandâ€™s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didnâ€™t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husbandâ€™s death wasnâ€™t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: As you sever the brain stem, you immediately notice a crystalline buildup in the cerebellum.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It shines and glistens in iridescent color.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It seems to reach deeper down.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is this reminiscent of any chemical buildup that can occur post-mortem or anything?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Samantha.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In such a short notice, you're at the limits of science yet again.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Without the slightest doubt this is nothing like you've ever seen before.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The fuck is this? I try to cut around the buildup without disturbing it.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: How did it get here?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Ha. Like I know! You don't know either!
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Whatever you're dealing with does not seem to be in touch with the reality you're a part of.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I touch the iridescent material with the tip of my scalpel.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: alekhin is afk
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: It scratches against it loudly and cracks it like the top layer of crÃ©me-brulee. It falls apart partially in fine dust and gets lost on the white tile floor.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha. Roll Sanity, blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a â€œ

catastrophic hemorrhage.â€ Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBIâ€™

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what sheâ€™d seen on her husbandâ€™

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldnâ€™t. They had already erased her husbandâ€™s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didnâ€™t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husbandâ€™s death wasnâ€™t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: Samantha looks at her hands to make sure they're not disappearing into a fine dust.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: It's already gone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Why did it do that to the scalpel and not his brain?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Out of the hundreds of gored limbs and crushed organs you had to piece back together, nothing was as extraordinary as what is in your hands.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I want to cut out a piece of his leg and drop it on the iridescent material.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Just a little.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You do so. It slides along with no effect.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Whatever this is, it can at least be contained by fleshâ€¦ Or dead fleshâ€¦ Or the dead flesh of this guy. Either way I'm not touching that.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: I get a dropper and try to transfer it to a glass vial.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You're already womanhandling it and it's not doing anything bad to your hands through nitrile gloves.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Pressing against it with steel or other metals might be it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A plastic bag should suffice.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yup. Should be easy to examine it in the lab.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: I think we got to the core of it, but I'd like to check the other wounds as well, if there are any.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You pack up and stove away the core of his brain. From the end of the cerebellum, all the way inside his amygdala.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No one will know.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: As for other wounds- you've already revealed everything you can that calls for cutting tools.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The cuts on his extremities are made by a sharp object, and the four neat holes on his chest cavity are passthrough via something curved, and possibly pointy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I pack up and get ready to stow the body away.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: On your way out, you sign off on the logs and run the mysterious thing inside the nickel bag through your fingers.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It hums softly.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Gonna be interesting to examine this thing in detail.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: It's 3PM. Actions.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I mean EVERYONE.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: VIA our secure communications I communicate my findings and wait for the next step.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Doug and Earle have been digging through files to see if any homicide cases have been recorded under similar circumstances, and they have failed to come up with any.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No you don't because I do that shizzle.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Samantha. It's a burner phone, you tell McCannon that something is up.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That's about all you tell as long as secure goes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon's lead. If I had my personal computer I'd be combing the chi-net for Tcho-Tcho information.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Relevant information will be communicated to AD Diaz LATERâ€¦..
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan, not much has changed since you did that the last time.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: How much of a hurry are the DEA in to get Domingo as of right now?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's a pain in the ass to try over a blackberry but ultimately possible, you don't find much.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In that case, he suggests we pull up on Domingo. Hardcore.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: How hardcore are we talking?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You don't know how much of a hurry they are in because none of you dropped by the field office, but you estimateâ€¦ not much.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're in New Mexico it's just one spic out of a million.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The county and state's list of active APBs is well into and through the double digits, so let's go make our contribution.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon did agree to do it black-bag style.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That means it might end in a different way than an arrest.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The boonies are right there.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We just need him for a little while.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Right on. EVERYONE. LIST ACTIONS. NO ACTION: YOU'RE JOINING IN THE SEARCH.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan volunteers either to drive or to carry a rifle. At least one person should be riding with a longarm.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Back in 2.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: khoka is afk
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: David will join in the search, with no particular other action in mind.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: alekhin is afk
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: khoka is back
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: What a strange way to phrase that question. Doug is a cop, you are aware. He knows his way around a gun.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Doug remains stoically unphased.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Earle is decent enough with guns and volunteers to join them with a rifle. He mentions that said rifles are now all select fire in passing and hopes nobody is too worked up about how that happened.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Okay.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan will drive the suburban.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Looks like everyone is riding in on this one.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: alekhin is back
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: All of you strap your vests on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: As for the heavier ones, there are some to go around but considering it might turn into a chaseâ€¦
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Anyone with a longarm needs to be wearing their SAPIs. That's policy.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon doesn't count on the spicaroo carrying anything heavier than a glock and having the guts to shoot instead of run.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Two ARs and a shotty. McCannon has an AR, Earle has an AR by the rite of passage and who gets the last?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I do!
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Just common sense, really.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: No one considering tazers, huh?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We don't play about the brown man.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The people WITHOUT the longarms should have the tazers.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: averagejoe22 is afk
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You've been driving around the hood for an hour now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You see two men coming out of Domingo's residential.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It seems to be himself along with another individual.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're parked a block away and they have not noticed the two cars. Yet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What is the approach?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A third figure is approaching. Teenager, black. Looks like he is buying some smack.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We can just roll up and grab him with three dudes doing a tactical exit and pointing guns while screaming levanta las manos at his ass. If the others give trouble, we shoot em'.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: They're going to either run or shoot, so we need to scoot up quick, dismount and throw them in the back. Who's driving the Corolla?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: It's manos-fucking-arriba, by the way.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
Toyota (up front)

Doug-driver
Cliff-shotgun
Earle - passenger

SUV (back)
Finnegan-driver
McCannon-shotgun
David-passenger
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We need fucking Domingo.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The other guy and the kid doesn't matter.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Domingo produces a nickel bag from his pants and gives it to the kid.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The other guy nods approvingly.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He came out of the building WITH him, remember.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Gotta take both." Finnegan says low.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Right then, this is going to be a head-on style thing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. Yes or no?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Corolla should pull past them, SUV parallel.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Yes, we're trimming the fat from the encounter with Occam's razor.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Let's do it quick.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: McCannon gives the go and both cars lurch forward, the Toyota coming to a screeing halt up front.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: LOADING.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: averagejoe22 is back
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The hostile party has the initiative. They are alerted.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "FUCK!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They will attempt to escape.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "OYE MARICON! HANDS IN THE FUCKING AIR!"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8
4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
messages.content:
CRITICAL FAILURE!

messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I AIN'T DO SHIT MANE!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Frank stares at McCannon and mentally begs him not to open fire.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: In another turn he will escape unless chased.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "GET THE FUCK OUTTA HERE, TYRONE!" McCannon shouts at the black kid.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: We don't have no business with Black Male Young
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He doesn't know or care if his name is Tyrone.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Dominigo crashes through the pile of garbage and drops something from his pant pocket.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Antonio is shielding for Domingo. You won't be able to shoot past him, you've lost sight.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Furthermoreâ€¦
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: HE'S REACHING!

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a â€œ

catastrophic hemorrhage.â€ Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBIâ€™

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what sheâ€™d seen on her husbandâ€™

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldnâ€™t. They had already erased her husbandâ€™s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didnâ€™t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husbandâ€™s death wasnâ€™t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: Doug BOLTS down the alleyway on his left and takes up a position, say, halfway down.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You're under half cover behind this trash bin.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I bet the others have it handled. Going to keep watch here if that guy ends up running down that way.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Earle. You're suppressed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He attempts to break said suppression.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Public POW.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Slightly overweight, brown hair combed to one side, chevron moustache.

a- Born 1980 in Paris Texas to a single mother. Rough upbringing led him to (mostly) forswear drugs and alcohol, developed a complex against middle America, 'hicks' etc.

- Became interested in computer science during the dot-com bubble and left home to study I.T at 18.

- Married in 2003 while working the help-desk at Cisco. Made the majority of his income at this time via cable piracy - running services that could decrypt smart cards, set-top boxes etc.

- Became interested in libertarianism and conspiracy culture at around this time, which tied into much of his hacking work; claims to have worked with Gary McKinnon, among others.

- Joined FBI Operational Technology division in 2005, in part for work experience and in part to enter the 'belly of beast' as far as his interests are concerned ('is the government really messing with the weather?' etc).

- Continues to work in this capacity alongside his side-hustles; regarded by colleagues as reliable, if a little eccentric.

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

6'5. Skinny. Blonde, blue eyes. Disproportionate long arms. Wide face and clavicles.

was investigating federal criminal audit

money laundering. lots of incoming subscriptions, library unexpected, unjustified for the area.

turns out its actually large library book club

tracked missing person, the book club president

investigated their domicile

found entire place ransacked and a book with most pages ripped out

found some pages that go against what he had learned during his cherished study of history

case ends inconclusive

started researching it in free time

DG's Carnivore-fork protocol detected his questions, silent alert is raised

he is contacted, debriefed thoroughly

several points he raises are analyzed and cross-referenced as useful deductions

investigation think-tank permits transfer of federal asset to DG

instruction and briefing commences, works on minor cases
