Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

6'5. Skinny. Blonde, blue eyes. Disproportionate long arms. Wide face and clavicles.

was investigating federal criminal audit

money laundering. lots of incoming subscriptions, library unexpected, unjustified for the area.

turns out its actually large library book club

tracked missing person, the book club president

investigated their domicile

found entire place ransacked and a book with most pages ripped out

found some pages that go against what he had learned during his cherished study of history

case ends inconclusive

started researching it in free time

DG's Carnivore-fork protocol detected his questions, silent alert is raised

he is contacted, debriefed thoroughly

several points he raises are analyzed and cross-referenced as useful deductions

investigation think-tank permits transfer of federal asset to DG

instruction and briefing commences, works on minor cases

messages.content: You feel like you just dodged that. You're unstoppable.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Something taps on your abdomen.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug, you may act.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Considering he's heard a loud exclamation of "TASER!" and people screaming bloody murder , then gunshots over there, Doug rounds the corner and tries to get as close as possible to Dominigo.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Ideally, pouncing on him in the same action.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Click the skill on your character sheetâ€¦ anyway that's a failure.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You run up just to the corner, but fail to round it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The old scar on your chest aches.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Lose your suppression, the shooter is dead.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You may act.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He runs to the alleyway feeling like a fat retard with no intent other than getting a gauge on the situation.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Behind Doug?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sure.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: You run about this much.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan. You're speeding.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yes.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: I will rush down towards the perp and try to tase him again.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Negative, reloading it would take a turn and you don't have an extra cartridge.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'll rush down shoot him in the legs, if possible, while yelling at him to stop. We have a medic on duty, after all.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Partial cover obscures his legs. You could go for the silhouette at a -20% but then you'd need to roll high enough damage to make it past the trash bin.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Or could I perhaps scare him into submission?
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Guy did his time and as just proven is not afraid of a white boy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If McCannon sees David raising his gun he will be yelling at him to NOT shoot.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: What exactly am I looking at right now? Did he topple over the trash out of sight?
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Does he look like he'll pop up in a second again?
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: No, he's there but partially covered.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can't gauge his future intentions without a roll.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: WHO AM I KIDDING? HE'S GONNA FUCKING KILL YOU BRO!!!
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: YOU JUST SHOT HIS SIDE MAN!
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 10 seconds to come up with an action or lose your turn.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I keep my gun pointed at him and clear the middle of the alley.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: You have partial cover only to your chest behind a structural column. You're aiming for a +20% on your next turn.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is the dumpster open or closed?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's open but splayed against the wall, doesn't obscure anything.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: How is Domingo positioned? Is he just laying down behind a toppled trash can?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He's behind it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Still on his feet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is he looking towards or away from us?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: WHAT DO YOU THINK.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'm surpressing this retard so others get a chance to pin him down.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You're shooting at his cover?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Well, it's an aluminium trash can with shit inside of it, even if it penetrates and pushes through the velocity should be slowed down enough by the time it reaches him that any wounds will be flesh ones.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: I just need him to keep his head down.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: I assume I can do this while moving forward a little.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Short or long burst?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Short burst.

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: David.

messages.content: Your vest absorbs the bullet nicely. However, not the kick behind it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It pins you right in the stomach.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your soft insides tolerate it, but barely.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're staggered. Your next action will be at a -20%. But you're still on your feet and breathing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug has a terrible premonition that some of his are taking fire. He rounds the corner carefully, weapon raised, and what he expects to see is the back of that beaner's neck, since he's probably facing away from him.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You realize immediately he's not this far up. You need to keep moving.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Keep moving I do.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Athletics, at a -20% due to the adrenaline.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Down the alley to the west, please.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

Ex-police officer from FLPD.

Medium height, pale man. Bright eyes contrasted by sleepless circles under. Moustache, no beard. Thick arms, contrasted by a relatively thin frame.

1990: 19 years old. Officially joined Police Force.

1996: 25 years old.

As Police: Responded to a missing persons crime. Investigated a mineshaft, where contact with something killed my team. The missing person re-appeared without any indication that they'd been missing shortly after.

Dismissed from force after 6 years service.

2000: Got my degree in Civil Engineering, and a certificate in demolition. Worked as a construction engineer for 4 years.

2004: At some point this year, someone showed him a photo of the blue dress. Then, the call. I have been made aware of Delta Green since this point, and performed small-scale tasks under the infrequent request. I have made no brushes with the truly unnatural, outside of the mineshaft. Additionally, I received a tip-off that the Federal Bureau had received word of my work in the force and wished to hire me on.

Joined as a Parole Agent.

2005: Completed work as a Parole Agent at a field office. After a year, I was transferred to D.C. due to extraordinary competence. It's likely some strings were pulled. I haven't questioned them.

2008: Present. I have worked in the FBI for 4 years and received only rare tip-offs from DG.

Ex-police officer from FLPD.

Medium height, pale man. Bright eyes contrasted by sleepless circles under. Moustache, no beard. Thick arms, contrasted by a relatively thin frame.

1990: 19 years old. Officially joined Police Force.

1996: 25 years old.

As Police: Responded to a missing persons crime. Investigated a mineshaft, where contact with something killed my team. The missing person re-appeared without any indication that they'd been missing shortly after.

Dismissed from force after 6 years service.

2000: Got my degree in Civil Engineering, and a certificate in demolition. Worked as a construction engineer for 4 years.

2004: At some point this year, someone showed him a photo of the blue dress. Then, the call. I have been made aware of Delta Green since this point, and performed small-scale tasks under the infrequent request. I have made no brushes with the truly unnatural, outside of the mineshaft. Additionally, I received a tip-off that the Federal Bureau had received word of my work in the force and wished to hire me on.

Joined as a Parole Agent.

2005: Completed work as a Parole Agent at a field office. After a year, I was transferred to D.C. due to extraordinary competence. It's likely some strings were pulled. I haven't questioned them.

2008: Present. I have worked in the FBI for 4 years and received only rare tip-offs from DG.

Slightly overweight, brown hair combed to one side, chevron moustache.

a- Born 1980 in Paris Texas to a single mother. Rough upbringing led him to (mostly) forswear drugs and alcohol, developed a complex against middle America, 'hicks' etc.

- Became interested in computer science during the dot-com bubble and left home to study I.T at 18.

- Married in 2003 while working the help-desk at Cisco. Made the majority of his income at this time via cable piracy - running services that could decrypt smart cards, set-top boxes etc.

- Became interested in libertarianism and conspiracy culture at around this time, which tied into much of his hacking work; claims to have worked with Gary McKinnon, among others.

- Joined FBI Operational Technology division in 2005, in part for work experience and in part to enter the 'belly of beast' as far as his interests are concerned ('is the government really messing with the weather?' etc).

- Continues to work in this capacity alongside his side-hustles; regarded by colleagues as reliable, if a little eccentric.

messages.content: He never had the makings of a varsity athlete.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: You run about this much, gun in hand.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're here, but there's a staircase leading downwards where you stand.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can see his neck up.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Without spending a turn, this is about what you see.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: So this is a cross-street, just not on the map, a staircase down and without getting out of the car that's what I can see?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You're out of the car you're standing at the head of the staircase now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'll cover down with my pistol and tell him to "DROP THE FUCKIN' GUN! DEA! DROP IT NOW!"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You're taking cover behind this scaffolding, still only having a clear shot on his head.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "CHINGA TU MADRE!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: As long as he can see and hear me. Taking it from both ends usually changes people's perspective on things.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You really didn't appreciate that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I don't have a good way to clear this distance without getting shot and no way to make him submit from range, so I'll simply pin him down and keep him suppressed. I shoot above his head by a feet or two.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Firearms at a -20%.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

6'5. Skinny. Blonde, blue eyes. Disproportionate long arms. Wide face and clavicles.

was investigating federal criminal audit

money laundering. lots of incoming subscriptions, library unexpected, unjustified for the area.

turns out its actually large library book club

tracked missing person, the book club president

investigated their domicile

found entire place ransacked and a book with most pages ripped out

found some pages that go against what he had learned during his cherished study of history

case ends inconclusive

started researching it in free time

DG's Carnivore-fork protocol detected his questions, silent alert is raised

he is contacted, debriefed thoroughly

several points he raises are analyzed and cross-referenced as useful deductions

investigation think-tank permits transfer of federal asset to DG

instruction and briefing commences, works on minor cases

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a â€œ

catastrophic hemorrhage.â€ Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBIâ€™

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what sheâ€™d seen on her husbandâ€™

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldnâ€™t. They had already erased her husbandâ€™s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didnâ€™t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husbandâ€™s death wasnâ€™t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

Criminal Investigative Division","employer":"FBI Criminal Investigative Division","nationality":"American - Florida","sex":"M","age":"37 - 22 Feb 1971","education":"UFHW Florida, B.A. in Civil Engineering"},"corruption":{"value":0,"haveSeenTheYellowSign":false,"gift":"","insight":""},"physicalDescription":"

Ex-police officer from FLPD.

Medium height, pale man. Bright eyes contrasted by sleepless circles under. Moustache, no beard. Thick arms, contrasted by a relatively thin frame.

1990: 19 years old. Officially joined Police Force.

1996: 25 years old.

As Police: Responded to a missing persons crime. Investigated a mineshaft, where contact with something killed my team. The missing person re-appeared without any indication that they'd been missing shortly after.

Dismissed from force after 6 years service.

2000: Got my degree in Civil Engineering, and a certificate in demolition. Worked as a construction engineer for 4 years.

2004: At some point this year, someone showed him a photo of the blue dress. Then, the call. I have been made aware of Delta Green since this point, and performed small-scale tasks under the infrequent request. I have made no brushes with the truly unnatural, outside of the mineshaft. Additionally, I received a tip-off that the Federal Bureau had received word of my work in the force and wished to hire me on.

Joined as a Parole Agent.

2005: Completed work as a Parole Agent at a field office. After a year, I was transferred to D.C. due to extraordinary competence. It's likely some strings were pulled. I haven't questioned them.

2008: Present. I have worked in the FBI for 4 years and received only rare tip-offs from DG.

Ex-police officer from FLPD.

Medium height, pale man. Bright eyes contrasted by sleepless circles under. Moustache, no beard. Thick arms, contrasted by a relatively thin frame.

1990: 19 years old. Officially joined Police Force.

1996: 25 years old.

As Police: Responded to a missing persons crime. Investigated a mineshaft, where contact with something killed my team. The missing person re-appeared without any indication that they'd been missing shortly after.

Dismissed from force after 6 years service.

2000: Got my degree in Civil Engineering, and a certificate in demolition. Worked as a construction engineer for 4 years.

2004: At some point this year, someone showed him a photo of the blue dress. Then, the call. I have been made aware of Delta Green since this point, and performed small-scale tasks under the infrequent request. I have made no brushes with the truly unnatural, outside of the mineshaft. Additionally, I received a tip-off that the Federal Bureau had received word of my work in the force and wished to hire me on.

Joined as a Parole Agent.

2005: Completed work as a Parole Agent at a field office. After a year, I was transferred to D.C. due to extraordinary competence. It's likely some strings were pulled. I haven't questioned them.

2008: Present. I have worked in the FBI for 4 years and received only rare tip-offs from DG.

messages.content: 10 minutes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan is going back for the SUV's medkit, hopefully it has a tourniquet. If this is even low enough for a TQ.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I got him! He's out! Out cold!"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'm going to move and do first aid with whatever I have on me, until we get a proper kit.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Optimistic, but this shit looks like a tourniquet won't cut it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sounds like a job for packing and a pressure bandage and a dream.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Surely we have a priority line for 911.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Apt, Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Calling 911 on this?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What happened to the concept of "black bag?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If we don't hurry up it's going to be a bodybag.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: In the meantimeâ€¦ due to the severity of the injury your IFAK won't actually guarantee any bonus. Roll Public First Aid.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cliff's roll?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David. Roll Alertness.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yes, Cliff.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Ms. Cliffe please make sure this man lives long enough for McCannon to torture him to death.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a â€œ

catastrophic hemorrhage.â€ Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBIâ€™

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what sheâ€™d seen on her husbandâ€™

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldnâ€™t. They had already erased her husbandâ€™s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didnâ€™t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husbandâ€™s death wasnâ€™t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

6'5. Skinny. Blonde, blue eyes. Disproportionate long arms. Wide face and clavicles.

was investigating federal criminal audit

money laundering. lots of incoming subscriptions, library unexpected, unjustified for the area.

turns out its actually large library book club

tracked missing person, the book club president

investigated their domicile

found entire place ransacked and a book with most pages ripped out

found some pages that go against what he had learned during his cherished study of history

case ends inconclusive

started researching it in free time

DG's Carnivore-fork protocol detected his questions, silent alert is raised

he is contacted, debriefed thoroughly

several points he raises are analyzed and cross-referenced as useful deductions

investigation think-tank permits transfer of federal asset to DG

instruction and briefing commences, works on minor cases

messages.content: David.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You notice the bag your guy dropped on his way out of here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's on the floor besides the dead guy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Oh, on that topic!
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Are you leaving him here?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Can't we take this guy to our guy?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Veterinarian was it?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Within the realm of possibility.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I pick up the bag "Mad Dog" dropped.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: It's daytime, however.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That complicates things.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Someone grab the dead fucker's phone."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: David. It's a bag of Skypes. Same bag as the ones you got from Damien, even.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "David! Get the guy's phone!"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: I grab the dead guy's phone and the bag and fuck off with the others.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content:
TWO MINUTE BATHROOM RUN.

- WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO WITH MAD DOG?
- WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO WITH PEREZ?
- WHO IS GOING WHERE?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If he's fucked up, he needs to go in the SUV backseat ziptied hard with someone sitting there. If we're feeling risky, the Corolla Team can case the house (since we need to do a passenger shuffle)
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Enough car space left to handle all of that? We sure as all are not leaving a dead body on the side of the road.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: I would hope we aren't.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: We are leaving a dead body on the side of the road.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: As you say,  boss.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Who gives a fuck this is the hood
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Yep.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Black bag asf
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Doug is given to understand "chiraq dialectics"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: We either drive this guy somewhere to get interrogated now or get him to the vet.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: We get him to the vet, he's dying.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Doctor's professional opinion
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: McCannon's call, I think.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He has three hours but he'll pass out.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Professional M.D. Opinion.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Call the vet, then.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Just drive him to the fucking ER, hospitals will let you stay bedside if you show badges.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Presumably we should vacate the crime scene and THEN call this guy
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: This isn't rocket science. Or any science.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Presumably we are doing this at once so it doesn't matter Mr. Earle
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Who's calling the vet.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Fuck the vet we go ER.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: we just said black bag MY NIGGA
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Your brainstorming is neat.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If DEA catches wind of this you'll be buried under a mountain of paperwork and statements.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan is right in that we can get them to ask exactly 0 questions by just flashing the badge.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The Vet is the best help you can get, since you didn't bother rigging a surgical theatre for yourselves.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We're not going to the fucking hospital for this.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: I didn't know the friendly did that kind of work. In that case, he's the best bet.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: We have the connect exactly for this type of work.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Righto. And the dead body?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: To the boonies I presume.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Throw the stiff in the Corolla trunk.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: In hindsight, yes.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's better if they think they skipped town.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's gonna make a huge mess in the back, but as long as no one opens itâ€¦
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We can clean out the carâ€¦
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Hispanics are coming out from windows around you. Clearly someone has heard and seen you, but are they willing to talk?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No, for all intents and purposes, nothing happened here. Cartel shit stays cartel shit.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You handcuff and legcuff Mad Dog and throw him in the back of the suburban. He is in no condition to fight for at least the next week.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And the body, it fits nicely in the Corolla trunk.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 4PM. You're on the road. Who is heading where?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon is heading with Cliffe to the vet. Somebody has to take the Corolla to the middle of nowhere and dump the body for wild animals.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Or dig a grave, if they're so inclined to manual labor.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Exactly, was gonna say that. The SUV holds 2 passengers with that guy lying in the back.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan is still driving the SUV, so it's to Happy Paw.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Negative, Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yeahâ€¦ Someone will have to deal with the body. Sounds like a two-man job.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: If Earle is involved in said job it's because he got goaded into it or drew a short straw.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: The sedan can comfortably fit the rest of you, and dead bodies don't want to get out of the trunk in case you want to drop someone off somewhere.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan, you're driving it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Call the shots.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can stop by a sporting goods store for some entrenching tools and I could recommend some nice places for a burial. Miles and miles of nothing up to Santa Fe and Arizona.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Northbound. We'll go on the highway 'til we can find some suitable frontage road to pull off on. We'll need a shovel from Home Depot or Lowes.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: No one wants to make another stop on the way?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The quicker we get this dead body out of our car and into the dirt, the better for everyone, Finnegan figures.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: More or less.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You drive north for about 3.5 hours, deep enough into the boonies that no one will know.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: To dig deep enough with 4 men to prevent scavengers will take another hour of work.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If it's time to get it off your chest, you four, it's now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan prefers not to say a fucking word about it.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: As does Doug. We're all nonchalant here like that.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: David. There's a golf ball sized black bruise right about to your left side, on soft flesh.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's yellow around.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Hurts to touch, but probably nothing big.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hell of a fraccasâ€¦" Earle mumbles, equal-parts disturbed and guilty at how useless he was for the whole ordeal.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: I pat it a bit and revel in the sensation, then ignore it from now on. I'll take a look later. I doubt any bones are broken.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: You're pretty sure nothing is broken.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doesn't take a doctor.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He had it coming anyway, I betâ€¦" None of this sits right with Doug.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: An hour passes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The hole is finally big enough for the body.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We checked his pockets already, right?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Yup. Keys, wallet, gun, burner phone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Unfortunately, he's bringing none of those things to the afterlife.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You could, if you wanted to, make the extra effort to prevent dental identification if this body was ever un-earthed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: However it's a nasty job and involves a shotgun.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I do it.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Christ. No--
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Doug doesn't want to look. Just doing what we have to doâ€¦
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Good man.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Jesus Christ."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Do the work.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You could also cut the fingertips off.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: But it will probably not be that quick, if ever.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: the flesh will probably rot quickly
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: David says, "Does anyone have a knife?"
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Just leave it. He's dead. We're four hours north of the city. By the time he gets dug up, nobody will remember these fake fucking names."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David nods.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Frank immediately holds David back lest he does something to make him vomit.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: David says, "Oh, I have my flashlight. Nevermind the shotgun."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Doug takes note of David jumping on the opportunity to mutilate a dead body.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: David proceeds to knock the man's teeth out with the heavy flashlight.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: David. You land a few heavy blows on the corpse but it does nothing to mutiliate the rear set of teeth.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He collects the few teeth, which will be scattered in completely unrelated places.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: So far, useless.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Stop, you- you fucking psychopath, man, Jesus. Someone help me throw him in."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "What kinda serial killer logic--"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Earle grabs the body by the legs.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: David says, "A partial dental match is better than a perfect one. This will suffice, in lieu of a more proper tool to finish the job. If you don't have any ideas, it's time to let this little spic enjoy the worm orgy."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Eager to keep David from turning the already grim sight into a trauma ward.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The thing. It's not in the breast pocket anymore.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You know what.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You're sick."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David turns towards Richard then says nothing.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Earle. Blind SAN Roll.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You heard me."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Earle's eyes suddenly resemble a doe staring down a truck.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "When you do a job, you have to do it properly."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: You're pretty sure this not-so dead guy snuck his fingers in your pocket to take it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The shotgun is laying across the rear seat of the car a few feet away from you. He needs to pay.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He rushes for said shotgun, an immediate and very noticeable change of heart.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "Whoa-- Frank, what's the big idea?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You reach for it in time. You have it trained on the hole and in the general direction of everyone else, before anyone else can draw their pistols.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "What the fuck are you do--"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Without a word to my very confused partners I aim at the dead man's face and fire.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "FUCK! â€¦That's one way to do it."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: -CLACK -CLACK -CLACK
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The guy's head turns into mistâ€¦
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: FINNEGAN, DOUG, DAVID, BLIND SAN ROLL.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David nods solemnly.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Feel explaining what that was to everyone, F--"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Dental records-- had to, y'know-- d-dental recordsâ€¦"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Followed by insensible blabbering.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: All three of you can feel it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Whatever you're doing here, whatever you have been doing, it totally does not have to do with how you've been trained, or raised.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Black bagging, body mutiliation, criminal organizations with no official recordâ€¦ what exactly are you all here for?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Everyone, roll a blind d8.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can feel your worldview dwindling under it's own hubristic weight like a poorly balanced house of cards.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's too late to return.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is this what it takes to keep the world spinning?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A perfectly intact molar, large in size, lands right next to your shoe.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're already getting ideas.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I take the tooth and pocket it, just like that. I look at the group with furrowed brows as I do so as though offended that they think I'm a maniac.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: He seems to calm down immediately, tossing the shotgun back in the car seat.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You are a maniac."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Now you can finish what you started.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He's holding his arms in the car and rocking about as though cold.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Doug can barely stand to look at the others. Is that what we're doing to make the world better? One spic, one head turned to chunks of gore at a time?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "You're fucking-- both of you, what the fuck are you thinking?" He points at Earle. "Put that in the fucking hole."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan. HUMINT Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can tell he is a stick of dynamite held just a bit above a candle. It would be wise to back off.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He's sweating like the sun is directly overhead and picks up a shovel. Let's get it done.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: The messy work ends as the sun is too ashamed to keep looking at you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Now, for the surgery.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon is standing in front of the door with a gun.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're lucky. No one was in when you came.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The Vet immediately closed up shop to attend to your guy, instead of dragging you into the "garage".
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha, it's looking like a good chance that this guy will live. Surgery, blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

CRITICAL SUCCESS!

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a â€œ

catastrophic hemorrhage.â€ Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBIâ€™

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what sheâ€™d seen on her husbandâ€™

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldnâ€™t. They had already erased her husbandâ€™s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didnâ€™t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husbandâ€™s death wasnâ€™t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: You've seen worse, yet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The operation will last a couple hours, but you got everything you need, enough ketamine to k-hole him for a month and a helping hand.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "How the fuck do you know him?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Do you have to know?"
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Do you even know who this guy is?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You brought him in during daytime too! Jesus!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We're out in no time."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: McCannon. You're overhearing this.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"Yeah you better be."

He tightens his surgical mask and reaches for a hemostat.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Two hours later, Samantha finishes up fishing out bits of clothing and copper off his flesh.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's about 9PM. He's alive, but unconscious due to anesthesia.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Exhausted, he pours out a coffee for himself.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Jesusâ€¦"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Should have seen him on the scene. Thought he wouldn't make it."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: He offers you a cup, McCannon. You've been quiet so far.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So who shot at him?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha looks over at McCannon.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: McCannon takes the cup and drinks, just raising his eyebrows once at that question.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Wait, let me get this straight."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You shot him?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Mhm," McCannon takes another sip.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He pinches the bridge of his nose.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Alright, you need to get the fuck out of here like, right now."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "As you say. Let's pack up and get out."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "He's asleep, but we should ziptie him to be safe."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content:
"Antibiotics, some naproxen, stomach pill to top it offâ€¦"

He's putting pill boxes in a bag.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Just get him out of here, you never showed up to this place."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "And next time do me the courtesy of giving a phone call."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We've never showed up here ever."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Anything else you wish to grab on your way out, Samantha?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon brushes past Cliff and whispers: "Lorazepam."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Well, I think our medkit has all we need. Maybe some sutures or disinfectantâ€¦
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: But that's it really.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "This is a fucking veterinary, dude."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I can get you some but it would take me a week or so."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The room is small. He heard you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Don't bother. We'll be long gone and by then I can handle it myself."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Yeah. Bye."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'm taking you're hauling his ass to the hideout.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Or someplace else?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: YES.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Likewise.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: I want to examine the thing
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: At a lab, maybe at the hospital?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Too late, try again tomorrow.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yeah saying it in advance
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: If you were a staff member you could, but you know. Anyway.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And the dig group? Off to some rest?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're aching all over from the shovelling and whatever the fuck that just happened.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan drives to the safehouse without a word to say to either of the unhinged freaks him and Doug and sharing the car with.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: It's about morning. There is one last thing I would like to do before finishing this session.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan. The tea shop.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Bringing anyone along?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Can I get McCannon, or is he indisposed?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Yes, if he can get some ridealongs. Better than leaving it untouched. This shit is already off the rails.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Anyone else?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug is invited; he seems like a normal human being with some integrity.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug's beat. But he's coming along.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Okay. Bathroom run, meanwhile enjoy discussing over cereal.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "â€¦Worst case, he's sick and we give him the scare of a lifetime. But I'm willing to bet a traditional medicine store here knows what the fuck "liao" means." He emphasizes the word with accent.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Lyaow?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "That's what they call it."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Right.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Here it is. It looks open this time.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No shit. Time flies.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Going in?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Afraid so.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Inside looksâ€¦ appropriately ethnic.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Hi! Welcome!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You want ginseng?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "There's actually a lot of data behind traditional eastern medicine." He tells Doug. "Good morning, no, no, actually, something for sleep." He indicates the other two agents.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You want sreep? I got lemon barm."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is this the same guy that was coughing his insides out a few days ago?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Pancreatic cancer?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He looks just fine.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That's what I was wondering myself.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: The girl is nowhere to be seen this time.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He coughs to himself a bit. Roll Awareness, blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No, just Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Alertness, or just /brd100?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: "Very good, what company?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Wangshu Steel 4. We mostly do business in California.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Good, come inside, I have a nice room for these kinds of occasions."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "My name is Shen Gonxu."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Rob Callahan. It's a pleasure.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan, you do agree to share the conversation with others once you're done right?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Unless its something extra secret.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They have a need to know, yes.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He's making some kind ofâ€¦ soup? It's not the usual tea greeting.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Continue in plain English.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon, Doug, you are clueless to what the fuck is going on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Absolutely so.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Where are you from? China is a very large country, I've only seen so little." He nods to his friends. "Gentlemen, this is mister Gonxu."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: As far as Doug is concerned, it just smells weird in here.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: This is some Fu Manchu bullshit here.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Uh, knee-haow, mister Gonxu."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Close to Cambodiaâ€¦ My village probably doesn't exist anymore because of that dog Maoâ€¦"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan nods solemnly. "It was a very hard time for many of my overseas colleagues."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You drink this soup, you live a thousand years."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He places a small bowl in front of you, foregoing the others.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It smells delicious, porky.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Mm. Is it a local recipe?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Chochao delicacy. Pork ganglia with soy."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It would be such an incredible faux-pas to refuse this. He glances at McCannon.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You take a sip of the soup with the Korean style long handle spoon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon is considering saying that he is Muslim or Jewish.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It has a very strong and savory umami flavor, with a powerful spicy punch.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan concocts an appropriate Chinese exclamation for satisfaction in food.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: For no reason in particular, the scene of Earle blowing a dead guys head off yesterday flashes before your eyes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Now, ahâ€¦ Don't mind me being so forwards, but I was actually looking for something in particular -- ahâ€¦ - that I heard about at a dinner last winter."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon is just idly picking at the soup.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Not really eating, kind of stirring it about absent-mindedly.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You don't realize it's actually pork brain and it does smell really good so it's your fucking loss, mmkay.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Huh, what have you heard?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well, he said it was called the 'nectar of heaven'. Now, we both know there are a dozen things in traditional medicine that might be called thatâ€¦" He laughs at his own joke.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You mean sacred Liao?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: His expression sours.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Oh, the younger generationâ€¦"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan snaps. "That was the word, yes."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "The kids don't understand it!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's no drug! It's sacred!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "They don't know that the Spirit does not take it lightly those who desecrate his gift!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He slams a fist on the table.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll INT.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That wordâ€¦ did that sound like God? As in Jesus?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well, I've heard that it was a very powerful medicine for particular illnesses. He never mentioned anyone misusing it."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He's resting his head on an elbow on the table, distressed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The kids are selling it on the street nowadaysâ€¦ Grown right here in yankee land!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It belongs to the Himalayas aloneâ€¦"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "On the street?" Finnegan pretends as hard as he can to be surprised at the mere idea. "Is it a religious object?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You know, I've heard of other problems like this down in South America. Once it's out of the hands of the people who know what to do with it, it becomes, well, you know."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "It's a sacrilege, son. Take it with no respect, you go insane."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Oh, I understand completely."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Only lamas can imbibe so muchâ€¦ but kids are taking it like candy!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So, it's an herb?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Sacred black lotus, prepared with alchemy."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You take some poria mushroom, wolfberry, jujube, astralagus, powder it, mix with goat milkâ€¦"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ohâ€¦ how would you know about it. Your generation is always aboutâ€¦" he makes a motion with his hands scrolling an iPhone
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon doesn't understand what fucking Chinese magic he's doing with his hands and is half a mind to blow his head smooth off, but controls himself out of great respect for his culture.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "I know, I know, it's ridiculous, the phones. It was an older gentleman from a material handling equipment company who mentioned it, himself. He said it did something incredible for his back after two surgeries in New York."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Liao brings youth back, but only in moderation."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Say, I think I know what you're here forâ€¦"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You wanna buy some?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He makes a pinching motion with his hands.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's gonna cost ya!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan offers a very coy smile. "Well, I wasn't expecting charity. But I'd like instructions, as well, if it's dangerous when misused."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I'll make a note for you, but you need to understand that the Spirit demands meditation lest it hungers."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: His smile widens up at the mention of you willing to pay, perhaps for whatever he is about to ask you of.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Three men in suits wanting to buy something is always a good sign.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll Alertness, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: You notice that his rear set of teeth is charcoal black, as if painted.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Up and down.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Curious. Maybe a Tcho-Tcho body art.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You feel like it might be a part of why they are called "knife smiles".
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Now time for business.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ten thousand dollar. Nickel bag. Other stuff on the side, for free."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We do happen to have a bit more than 'ten thousand dorra' I think.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Mm. Well, of course, I'll come back with the money." He adjusts his glasses. "When you mean spirit, do you mean, ahâ€¦ Shennong?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Ten bands for a nickel bag of anything short of diamonds is insano, but when the money's freeâ€¦
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "No, you mispronounce it."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You may not behold the goddess before contemplating on a perfectly empty space first. It's sacrilege."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: â€¦ What is he sayingâ€¦
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It sounds like he's describing meditation, like he said earlier.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You must focus on absolute emptiness so goddess has nothing to feed on in your mind, son. Do this before imbibing the tea."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I've been taking some excellent meditation classes in Shenzen." He smiles. "What do you mean by feed? I don't mean to pry, only that it's an unusual choice of words."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You ask too much."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Right. Of course. I'll be back with the money."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Not before you correctly pronounce her name."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Tell your friends to close your eyes and focus on blackness."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan nods. "Right, right."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug nods similarly. But not a word of this did he understand.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Should probably ask about the "focusing on blackness" thing later. Someone like McCannon.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Yeah, don't.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The air feels dead. Colors seem to drown.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan, you three are holding hands, daisy chained together around the table.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The whiter ones among you seemed to have understood the assignment.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Without you noticing, the man gets up from his chair and goes over to the framed caligraphy on the wall.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
With a tug, he takes it off to reveal the savage portrait.

"Behold, the goddess Shukoran!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan. The last thing you remember before passing out from a panic attack is releasing a torrent of cold sweat.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Reverberations Session 4 - End
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Thanks for playing!
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
